</md></sn><sn><md>### Trojan War {.text-center}

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
Greek mythology’s one of the most important parts is `the Trojan War`. The beginning of the Trojan War happened due to a `quarrel among three Greek goddesses`. The three goddesses were `Athena, Hera, and Aphrodite`. The one who actually ++started the dispute++ among them was another goddess `Eris`. The reason behind the conflict was quite logical — `Eris is the goddess of chaos and discord`. She gave a `golden apple` to these three goddesses, which is sometimes referred to as the “Apple of Discord” and had the inscription written on it: `for the fairest one`. As a result, all three goddesses started claiming the apple for themselves. The gods did not dare to judge the beauty of the three goddesses. Eventually, Zeus gave the responsibility of `choosing the most beautiful one` to `Prince Paris of Troy`, who was *an ordinary human being*. Paris declared `Aphrodite as the most beautiful`, and in return, Aphrodite promised him `the love of the most beautiful woman in the world`. At that time, the most `beautiful mortal woman was Helen`, who was ++the wife of King Menelaus of Sparta in Greece++. 
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://paleothea.com/media/images/paris-judging-the-beauty-contest-between-hera-athena-and-aph_46189f.jpg)
:::
:::


:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://media.gettyimages.com/id/464448037/photo/paris-abducting-helen-c1782-c1784-artist-gavin-hamilton.jpg?s=594x594&amp;w=gi&amp;k=20&amp;c=9nuYXnGZfZ8Tj0w9SFKZrRpQ0tJW4BAO7gGvIvTQnd0=)
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
The war began when `Paris abducted Helen and fled to Troy`. `Menelaus called his brother Agamemnon`, the king of Mycenae, to go to war and bring Helen back. `Agamemnon, along with his Achaean forces`, marched toward Troy. For nearly `ten years`, Agamemnon’s army surrounded the city of Troy from all sides. In that bloody war, `Achaean heroes Achilles, Ajax, and Trojan heroes Paris and his brother Hector were killed`. Eventually, `the Greek warriors` used ++the Trojan Horse++ as a trick `to enter the city of Troy`. The Trojans, thinking it was just a wooden horse, made the biggest mistake by bringing the “Trojan Horse” inside the city.
:::
:::


:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
This story is so fascinating and thrilling that it holds a significant place in both `Greek and Roman literature` as **the Trojan War**. Especially through the two epics of `the great poet Homer`, `The Iliad` and `The Odyssey`, this ++romantic tragedy++ has been immortalized. In ancient times, Greeks believed that the Trojan War was a historical event. They thought it happened around `1300 or 1200 BCE`. Many also believed that both the city of Troy and the war were purely mythical stories. However, the story of the Trojan War gained major popularity when `in 1868 Heinrich Schliemann and Frank Calvert, two archaeologists, discovered the city of Troy in the Hisarlik region of Turkey`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
