:::
:::
</md></sn><sn><md>#### Philosophy

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-9
The greatest *contribution* of the Greeks was in the field of `philosophy`. One of the ++earliest famous philosophers++ was `Thales`. Instead of mythological explanations, Thales was the first to `explain the natural cause of a solar eclipse`. Gradually, a ++rational group of philosophers++ emerged in Greece known as the `Sophists`.
:::
:::.col-12 .col-md-3
![img](https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTfisvlpJjKiFHlkv2DCupyW6Mdr1hYAI6l6w&amp;s)
:::
:::

`Protagoras` was one of the earliest and most ++famous Greek philosophers of the Sophist movement++. He is widely known not for explaining the mysteries of creation, but for focusing on humans as the standard of knowledge and contributing to philosophy and linguistics. He believed:

&gt; ‘Man is the measure of all things’.



---

**Teacher–Student Relationship of Philosophers**

![img](https://www.shutterstock.com/image-photo/succession-ancient-greek-teachers-students-600w-31486639.jpg)
---


:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
**Socrates**

`Socrates` was one of the most ++famous philosophers++ of Greece. For *protesting against unjust rule*, the ruling authority of Athens `sentenced him to death` in 399 BCE by forcing him to drink poison made from hemlock. His `last words` were:

&gt; ‘Crito, I owe a cock to Asclepius, will you remember to pay the debt?’
&gt; *(“Crito, Asclepius is owed a rooster; don’t forget to repay the debt”)*

`Asclepius` is the Greek ++god of healing++. From Socrates last words, it is understood that he `believed death to be a form of healing and the liberation` of the soul from the body. Socrates is known as the `teacher of all wise men`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8c/David_-_The_Death_of_Socrates.jpg)
:::
:::

Famous quotes of Socrates
* Know thyself.
* Slanderers do not hurt me because they do not hit me.
* Education is the kindling of a flame, not the filling of a vessel.
* I die, you to live — which is better only God knows.
* An unexamined life is not worth living.
* Knowledge is virtue.

---

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-4
![img](https://cdn.britannica.com/75/177675-050-BFA26F0C/detail-Aristotle-School-of-Athens-Plato-Raphael.jpg)
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-8
**Plato**

`Plato`, the ++student of Socrates++, elevated Greek philosophy to a higher level. He wrote the famous book `The Republic` to preserve his ideas. In 386 BCE, Plato founded the ++philosophical school++ `Akademia`. He also wrote `Dialogues of Socrates`, based on Socratic teachings.
Famous quote of Plato

* Virtue is Knowledge and Education is the main thing to acquire virtue.
:::
:::


---

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
**Aristotle**

`Aristotle`, the ++student of Plato++, was also a great philosopher. One of his famous works is `Politics`. He was the ++founder++ of the `Lyceum` and also served as the ++tutor of Alexander the Great++.

**Famous quotes of Aristotle:**
* Man is by nature a social and political being.
* He who cannot live in society is either a beast or a god.
* Law is reason free from passion.
* A constitution is a way of life prescribed by the state.
* Courage, strength, and desire are unequally distributed by nature among humans.
* The state is an extension of the family.
* Man is by nature a political animal.
:::

