:::.col-12 .col-md-7
Greeks also made significant ++contributions++ to the field of `history writing`. The Greek historian `Herodotus` is known as the  ++Father of History++. He was born around 484 BCE in `Halicarnassus`, modern-day `Bodrum` in Turkey. His famous work is `The Histories`. This book describes the `Greco-Persian Wars` of 490 BCE. 
:::
:::

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-9
Another renowned Greek historian was `Thucydides`, who is known as the ++Father of Scientific History++.
